== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=Greenflashlight.png|caption=Artistic representation of a maxiflashie and a miniflashie.|align=right}}
'''Object 25''', also known as "Flashies", are electronic devices found in different levels, resembling green tactical flashlights from [[The Frontrooms]]. On average, they weigh about 120 grams and can range in length from 7 cm to 35 cm; those under 10 cm are known as '''"miniflashies"''', while those 10 cm or longer are called '''"maxiflashies"'''. Miniflashies are less effective, but they are more portable than '''maxiflashies'''.

These gadgets can be rarely located in levels with a high amount of cul-de-sacs and turns. In those levels, '''flashies''' are found lying on the floor or in closed containers, such as cardboard boxes or wooden drawers. '''Flashies''' are often overlooked by wanderers as they can be mistaken for normal flashlights. The only way to distinguish them is their unnaturally perfect cylindrical shape.

== Usage ==
'''Flashie'''<nowiki>'s</nowiki> function is turning a part of the walls transparent so that wanderers can see through them wherever the '''flashie''' is directed. However, the walls look completely opaque to the entities. This allows people to discover dangerous entities easily without being caught.

'''Flashies''' operate expectedly in levels with stable geometry, such as [[Level 1]], [[Level 2]], or [[Level 3]]. But in levels with inconsistent, shifting, or morphing geometries like [[Level 0]] or [[The End]], '''flashies''' usually give inaccurate results, which means the result shown is completely different from what is actually behind the wall. These errors may occur because '''flashies''' are unable to predict what is behind a wall with unstable geometry.

When a '''flashie''' is pointed at an infinitely thick wall like the walls of [[Level 2]], the '''flashie''' shows an empty black void as it cannot detect the back of the wall, which is non-existent. However, as long as the walls have a certain finite thickness, '''flashies''' are able to show what is behind the back of the wall. The same applies when the '''flashie''' is pointed at [[The Void]] or walls with nothing but a void behind.

<div style="background-color:#ff0303; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:10px solid #a80202; border-radius: 5px">
=== Red Flashies ===
{{Blurimage|file=Redflashlight.png|caption=Red flashies. Note that their lights are way stronger than green's.|align=right}}
Since the discovery of '''flashies''', '''red flashies''' are the only special variant of '''Object 25'''. A '''red flashie''' takes the shape of a black aluminium flashlight with a rheostat at the tip of it. They also vary in different sizes, so they can be grouped into '''maxiflashies''' and '''miniflashies'''.

'''Red flashies''' are significantly rarer and harder to find compared to regular '''flashies''' since they only appear in blind spots, such as the corner of a room, behind a door, or under a table. '''Red flashies''' can sometimes be misidentified as ordinary flashlights as well as '''green flashies'''.

'''Red flashies''' work similarly to standard flashies, but with an extra function of emitting a strong red light. The rheostats at the tip of them allow them to toggle between releasing a powerful light and revealing what is behind walls. Their lights can scare off entities that are sensitive to light, especially Smilers.</div>

== Locations ==
=== Green Variants ===
*These '''flashies''' can be found in levels with a high number of turns or a maze-like structure. For example, [[Level 0]], [[Level 5]], [[Level 8]], etc.
*Levels with an extremely low concentration of objects.
*'''Maxiflashies''' can appear on tables in stable levels.
*'''Miniflashies''' have a slim chance to appear in drawers in indoor levels.
<div style="background-color:#ff0303; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:10px solid #a80202; border-radius: 5px">
=== Red Variants ===
*They can be found in any level where '''green flashies''' are present. However, they hide in obscure places where they are harder to spot.
</div>
